[[File:Gillan tbilisi 02.jpg|thumb|The British hard-rock legend [[Ian Gillan]] and his wife Bron, dressed in Georgian national costumes, in [[Tbilisi]] during Gillan's 1990 visit to the [[Soviet Union]].]]
A '''Kartvelophile''' ({{lang-ka|ქართველოფილი}}) is a person who is fond of, admires or loves [[Georgian culture]], [[Georgian history]], [[Georgian language]], [[Georgian cuisine]], [[Georgian people]] or [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] in general or even exhibits [[Georgian nationalism]] in spite of not being an ethnic Georgian. Such love of Georgia and everything Georgian is called "Kartvelophilia". Its opposite is [[Kartvelophobia]].

==Typical interests of Kartvelophiles==
[[Georgian wine]], [[Georgian cuisine]], [[Georgian language]], [[Georgian scripts]], [[Georgian calligraphy]]

