{{Infobox fragrance |Name = Égoïste |Image = Égoïste.jpg |Image size = 150 |Caption = |Endorsed by = [[Jacques Polge]] |Type = |Notes = |Released = 1990 |Label = [[Chanel]] |Tagline = |Predecessor = |Successor = |Flankers = [[Platinum Egoiste|Platinum Égoïste]] |URL = [http://www.chanel.com/fr_FR/parfums-beaute/Parfums-%C3%89go%C3%AFste-90089 Égoïste at chanel.com] }} '''Égoïste''' is a men's perfume produced by French fashion house [[Chanel]].<ref name="BusinessWeek - 11 November 2011 - Paris retrospective celebrates ad man Goude">{{cite news|url=http://www.businessweek.com/ap/financialnews/D9QUL8881.htm |archive-url=https://archive.is/20131025111516/http://www.businessweek.com/ap/financialnews/D9QUL8881.htm |dead-url=yes |archive-date=25 October 2013 |title=Paris retrospective celebrates ad man Goude |last=Barchfield |first=Jenny |date=11 November 2011 |work=[[BusinessWeek]] |publisher=Bloomberg L.P. |accessdate=25 October 2013 }}</ref><ref name="chanel.com - Égoïste - Chanel Fragrance">{{cite web |url=http://www.chanel.com/en_US/fragrance-beauty/Fragrance-%C3%89go%C3%AFste-88418|title=Égoïste - Chanel Fragrance |publisher=Chanel |accessdate=25 October 2013}}</ref> It was created by perfumer [[Jacques Polge]].<ref name="Philippine Daily Inquirer - 18 June 2004 - Master of redolence: Jacques Polge is the nose of Chanel, responsible for the brand's hit scents">{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=Ulc1AAAAIBAJ&sjid=iSUMAAAAIBAJ&pg=1868,1320623&dq=chanel+egoiste+polge&hl=en|title=Master of redolence: Jacques Polge is the nose of Chanel, responsible for the brand's hit scents |last=Burgos |first=Rowena |date=18 June 2004 |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |accessdate=25 October 2013}}</ref> The perfume was released in 1990.<ref name="El Universal (Mexico City) - 30 January 2007 - Mademoiselle Chanel rompió esquemas">{{cite news |url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estilos/52020.html|title=Mademoiselle Chanel rompió esquemas |last=Ramírez |first=Claudia |date=30 January 2007 |work=[[El Universal (Mexico City)|El Universal]] |language=Spanish |accessdate=25 October 2013}}</ref> The word is [[French language|French]] for "egoist", which means selfish or self-centered.
Commercials for the perfume have been directed by [[Jean-Paul Goude]].
==Product history== Based on [[Bois des Îles]], Égoïste is the first male perfume with [[sandalwood oil]] as its main note. Another of its components is [[ambrette seed]]. The fragrance's name when it was introduced domestically in the 1980s was Bois Noir, French for "Black Wood", a name that was originally used in the working stage. Prior to its 1990 international launch, the product was [[rebranding|rebranded]] because Chanel's marketing department did not like the Bois Noir name. The company had to purchase the rights to use the Égoïste name from photography magazine publisher Nicole Wisniak.<ref name="jpolgehint">[http://hintmag.com/post/qampa-with-the-legendary-chanel-perfumer-jacques-polge--september-02-2010 Gaboué, Stéphane. "Q&A with Legendary Chanel Perfumer Jacques Polge," Hint (web fashion magazine), Thursday, September 2, 2010.] Retrieved December 2, 2017</ref>
==Advertising== The centerpiece of Chanel's advertising campaign to launch Égoïste first in Europe in April 1990 and in the United States one year later was a 30-second commercial, in French without subtitles, directed by [[Jean-Paul Goude]] and costing more than $1 million US to make.<ref name="Kanner">{{cite magazine |last=Kanner |first=Bernice |title=Scents of Accomplishment: Society and Égoïste |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/New_York_Magazine.html?id=DukCAAAAMBAJ&q=%22le+cid%22+egoiste |work=New York Magazine |date=18 March 1991 |pages=20–21}}</ref><ref name="Foltz">{{cite news |last=Foltz |first=Kim |title=New Chanel Men's Scent Gets Provocative Campaign |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/03/05/business/the-media-business-advertising-new-chanel-men-s-scent-gets-provocative-campaign.html |work=The New York Times |date=5 March 1991 |page=D22}}</ref> It was filmed in a desert outside of [[Rio de Janeiro]]. A stucco facade inspired by that of the [[InterContinental Carlton Cannes Hotel]] was constructed by 300 workers in less than four weeks.{{Citation needed|date=October 2018}}
Its primary feature was 36 [[balcony|balconies]] situated four high and nine wide, each with shuttered doors. With "[[Dance of the Knights]]" from Sergei Prokofiev's ballet ''Romeo and Juliet'' as its background music, the film opens in [[black and white]] with a sequence of women dressed in [[ball gown]]s shouting lines adapted from Pierre Corneille's tragicomic play ''[[Le Cid]]'':{{refn|name=Kanner}}
{{quote|''Égoïste. Où es-tu? Montre-toi misérable! Prends garde à mon courroux! Je serai implacable! Ô rage! Ô désespoir! Ô mon amour trahi! N'ai-je donc tant vécu que pour cette infamie? Montre toi, Égoïste!'' (Egoist. Where are you? Show yourself, miserable one! Beware of my wrath! I will be relentless! O anger! O despair! O my betrayed love! Have I lived so long for this infamy? Show yourself, Egoist!){{efn|The original lines from Act 1, Scene 4 of the play are, "Ô rage! Ô désespoir! Ô viellesse ennemie! N'ai-je donc tant vécu que pour cette infamie?" ("O anger! O despair! O age my enemy! Have I lived simply to know this infamy?").<ref>[http://www.crdp-strasbourg.fr/je_lis_libre/livres/Corneille_LeCid.pdf ''Le Cid'' de Pierre Corneille &ndash; In Libro Veritas.] Retrieved December 4, 2017</ref><ref>[http://www.poetryintranslation.com/PITBR/French/LeCidActI.php ''Le Cid'' by Pierre Corneille &ndash; Poetry in Translation.] Retrieved December 4, 2017</ref>}} }}
The ad won a Gold Lion award at the [[International Advertising Festival]] held at Cannes.{{refn|name=Kanner}}{{refn|name=Lazarus}} Égoïste's sales exceeded initial projections by 35 to 40 percent fifteen months after the international launch.<ref name="Lazarus">{{cite news |last=Lazarus |first=George |title=Chanel`s Egoiste Doubles Its Appeal |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1991-06-26/business/9102260237_1_egoiste-chanel-boutiques-arie-kopelman|website=Chicago Tribune |date=26 June 1991}}</ref>
